<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Fire is an important process in maintaining stands of <i>Leymus condensatus</i>, which wax and wane throughout the landscape because of variable fire regimes. Suppressed individuals of <i>L. condensatus </i>may persist under canopies of coastal scrub and woodland for many years. The rhizomatous nature of <i>L. condensatus </i>enables it to spread quickly after fire removes the overstory.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
